#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:5
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:7
msgid ""
"Cloth simulation is one of the hardest aspects of CG, because it is a deceptively simple real-world item that is "
"taken for granted, yet actually has very complex internal and environmental interactions. After years of "
"development, Blender has a very robust cloth simulator that is used to make clothing, flags, banners, and so on. "
"Cloth interacts with and is affected by other moving objects, the wind and other forces, as well as a general "
"aerodynamic model, all of which is under your control."
msgstr ""
"布料模拟是CG最难的方面之一，因为它是一个看似简单的真实世界的物品，被认为是理所当然的，但实际上却具有着非常复杂的内"
"部和环境相互作用。 经过多年的开发，Blender拥有非常强大的布料模拟器，用于制作服装，旗帜，横幅等。布与其他移动物体，"
"风和其他力量以及一般空气动力学模型相互作用并受其影响，所有这些都在您的控制之下。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:21 ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:31
msgid "Cloth example."
msgstr "布料例子。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:26
msgid "Cloth on carved wooden men (made by motorsep)."
msgstr "雕刻木人上的布料（由motorsep制作）。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:33
msgid ""
"A piece of cloth is any mesh, open or enclosed, that has been designated as cloth. The *Cloth* panels are located "
"in the *Physics* tab and consist of three panels of options. Cloth is either an open or closed mesh and is mass-"
"less, in that all cloth is assumed to have the same density, or mass per square unit."
msgstr ""
"一块布是指定为布料的任何网格，开放或封闭的。*布料*面板位于 *物理* 选项卡中，由三个选项面板组成。 布料可以是开放的"
"或闭合的网状物，没有质量，因为所有的布料被认为具有相同的密度或每平方单位的质量相同。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:38
msgid ""
"Cloth is commonly modeled as a mesh grid primitive, or a cube, but can also be, for example, a teddy bear. "
"However, Blender's :doc:`soft body system </physics/soft_body/index>` provides better simulation of closed "
"meshes; Cloth is a specialized simulation of fabrics."
msgstr ""
"布料通常建模为基本网格或立方体，但也可以是例如一只泰迪熊。然而，Blender的 :doc:`软体系统 </physics/soft_body/"
"index>` 提供了更好的封闭网格模拟；布料是一种专门的织物模拟。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"Once the object is designated as Cloth, a Cloth :doc:`modifier </modeling/modifiers/index>` will be added to the "
"object's modifier stack automatically. As a :doc:`modifier </modeling/modifiers/index>` then, it can interact "
"with other modifiers, such as *Armature* and *Smooth*. In these cases, the ultimate shape of the mesh is computed "
"in accordance with the order of the modifier stack. For example, you should smooth the cloth *after* the modifier "
"computes the shape of the cloth."
msgstr ""
"一旦物体被指定为布料，一个布料 :doc:`修改器 </modeling/modifiers/index>` 将自动添加到物体的修改器中。作为一个 :"
"doc:`修改器 </modeling/modifiers/index>`，那么它可以与其他修改器进行交互，例如 *骨架* 和 *平滑*。 在这些情况下，网"
"格的最终形状根据修改器的顺序进行计算。 例如，平滑布料操作应该在修改器计算布料的形状 *之后*。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:48
msgid ""
"So you edit the Cloth settings in two places: use the Physics buttons to edit the properties of the cloth and use "
"the Modifier stack to edit the Modifier properties related to display and interaction with other modifiers."
msgstr ""
"因此，您可以在两处编辑布料设置：使用“物理”按钮编辑布料的属性，或使用“修改器”编辑与其他修改器显示与交互相关的修改器"
"属性。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:52
msgid ""
"You can *Apply* the Cloth Modifier to freeze, or lock in, the shape of the mesh at that frame, which removes the "
"modifier. For example, you can drape a flat cloth over a table, let the simulation run, and then apply the "
"modifier. In this sense, you are using the simulator to save yourself a lot of modeling time."
msgstr ""
"您可以*应用*布料修改器来冻结或锁定当前帧处的网格形状，这样会删除修改器。 例如，您可以在桌子上铺上一块平布，让模拟"
"运行，然后应用修改器。从这个意义上说，您正在使用模拟器来节省大量建模时间。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:57
msgid ""
"Results of the simulation are saved in a cache, so that the shape of the mesh, once calculated for a frame in an "
"animation, does not have to be recomputed again. If changes to the simulation are made, you have full control "
"over clearing the cache and re-running the simulation. Running the simulation for the first time is fully "
"automatic and no baking or separate step interrupts the workflow."
msgstr ""
"模拟的结果保存在缓存中，以便一旦在动画中的计算出来的每一帧的网格形状不必再次重新计算。如果对模拟进行了更改，您可以"
"完全控制清除缓存并重新运行模拟。第一次运行模拟是完全自动的，没有烘焙或单独的步骤会中断工作流程。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:62
msgid ""
"Computation of the shape of the cloth at every frame is automatic and done in the background; thus you can "
"continue working while the simulation is computed. However, it is CPU-intensive and depending on the power of "
"your PC and the complexity of the simulation, the amount of CPU needed to compute the mesh varies, as does the "
"lag you might notice."
msgstr ""
"计算每一帧的布料形状是自动的，并在后台完成；因此您可以在模拟计算时继续工作。但是，这很占用CPU，并且取决于PC的性能"
"和模拟的复杂性，计算网格变化所需的CPU占用量会有所不同，同样您可能会注意到的电脑卡顿也会不同。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:67
msgid "Do not jump ahead"
msgstr "不要往前快进"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:69
msgid ""
"If you set up a cloth simulation but Blender has not computed the shapes for the duration of the simulation, and "
"if you jump ahead a lot of frames forward in your animation, the cloth simulator may not be able to compute or "
"show you an accurate mesh shape for that frame, if it has not previously computed the shape for the previous "
"frame(s)."
msgstr ""
"如果您设置了布料模拟，但Blender尚未计算模拟持续时间内的形状，并且如果您在动画中向前快进了大量帧数，且Blender之前没"
"有计算出前一帧或前几帧的形状，布料模拟器可能无法计算或显示出那一帧精确的网格形状。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:76
msgid "Workflow"
msgstr "工作流程"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:78
msgid "A general process for working with cloth is to:"
msgstr "制作布料的一般过程是："

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:80
msgid "Model the cloth object as a general starting shape."
msgstr "建模出布料物体作为一般起始形状。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:81
msgid "Designate the object as a \"cloth\" in the *Physics* tab of the Properties editor."
msgstr "将该物体指定为属性编辑器的*物理*选项卡中的“布料”。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:82
msgid ""
"Model other deflection objects that will interact with the cloth. Ensure the Deflection modifier is last on the "
"modifier stack, after any other mesh deforming modifiers."
msgstr "模拟与布料相互作用的其他偏转对象。确保修改器堆栈上的形变修改器位于任何其他网格变形修改器之后。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:84
msgid "Light the cloth and assign materials and textures, UV unwrapping if desired."
msgstr "给布料添加灯光并指定材料和纹理，如果需要，可进行UV展开。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:85
msgid "If desired, give the object particles, such as steam coming off the surface."
msgstr "如果需要，可以给予物体颗粒，如从表面上掉下来的蒸汽。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:86
msgid ""
"Run the simulation and adjust Options to obtain satisfactory results. The Timeline editors VCR controls are great "
"for this step."
msgstr "运行模拟并调整选项以获得满意的结果。 时间轴编辑器VCR控制对于此步骤非常有用。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:88
msgid "Optionally age the mesh to some point in the simulation to obtain a new default starting shape."
msgstr "可选的操作是，将网格动画到模拟中的某个时间点，以获取新的开始动画的形状。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:89
msgid "Make minor edits to the mesh on a frame-by-frame basis to correct minor tears."
msgstr "在逐帧的基础上对网格进行较小的编辑，以修正较小的撕裂。"

#: ../../manual/physics/cloth/introduction.rst:93
msgid "To avoid unstable simulation, ensure that the cloth object does not penetrate any of the deflection objects,"
msgstr "为避免模拟不稳定，请确保布料物体不会穿透任何偏转物体。"
